cID=42.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hunting Ice Giants</span><hr size=1> Just hit lvl 49 and thought I would try the Ice Giants.  After hunting the middle giant (Perma zone is close by) and dying once, I need some advice.  I had thought the earth pet would be better than water as the water spell attack is cold based.  I do *not* have Elemental Maelstrom (I realize it has a lower taunt) and have little ideas about where to get it, ease of getting it, or price if I buy it.<br>
<br>
Spells used were rain of swords, SoS, and Lava bolt.   Any ideas to reduce risk or data on the Maelstrom spell?  Thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uchakkolio.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chakkolio</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#333333>(12/9/01 8:00:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE: Hunting Ice Giants</span><hr size=1> i would see if u can get a higher lvl mage or a mage with high research to make u the 49 fire pet... the DS it casts on itself rocks, along with its fire-based attacks, and ur Lava bolts... IGs shouldnt be too tough.<br>
<br>
Elemental Maelstrom drops off Wurms in Great Divide, so either go hunt some wurms, or just /auc in GD and im sure ull get some offers for the spell... thats how i got mine, and i only paid 30pp for it.. not bad, since its a dropped spell and i coulda had someone try to overcharge me for it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usrial.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Srial</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(12/19/01 2:16:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hunting Ice Giants</span><hr size=1> I paid 50 platinum for my elemental maelstrom spell, but I agree it could be had for less.  Auctioning in the Great Divide is definately the best way to find it.  (I did 40-43 in the easternwastes so every time I passed throught the divide I just auctioned and after 6 or 7 trips through got one.)  I've seen people auctioning the spell for 100-200 in other zones so be careful... Probably the same idiots who will one day try to charge me 20k for a Quill cloak MQ.<br>
<br>
You may also want to check the vendors in Thrugadin.   I often see drop only spells on them, although I've never seen the magician ones there I have often seen enchanter dropped spells on merchants.  <br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
<br>
